{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Dependencies (STACKED — review with --ref HEAD)\nDocuments the whole identity epic shipped by ddbe/4e9d/bde5/e165/264f/2f13/3183 (all\ncommitted on this branch). Review with `--ref HEAD`.\n\n## Context\nDocument the authenticated-identity model end-to-end so operators and agents can\nadopt it, and record the load-bearing architectural decisions as an ADR.\n\n## What\n### 1. `docs/identity.md` — the identity model end-to-end\nA new operator/agent guide covering, with concrete `rebar identity …` examples:\n- **The `identity` entity** (`src/rebar/…`): a gate/graph/Jira-sync-exempt ticket-type\n  (like `session_log`) holding name, email, `{provider, external_id}` mappings, and\n  public keys; the `.rebar/current_identity` self-identity pointer.\n- **Tiers**: real identities vs. `placeholder` ghosts (inbound-minted, idempotently\n  upgraded) — how to tell them apart (`is_placeholder`) and how ghosts get promoted.\n- **Event attribution**: every local event carries denormalized `author`/`author_email`\n  + optional `author_id`; replay back-compat.\n- **Authorship attestation** (`rebar.authorship.v1`): SSHSIG over the foundation attest\n  substrate; trust root = the identity's in-band keys.\n- **Key rotation / era-scoping**: TOFU genesis, signed add/revoke, epoch-scoped validity\n  (`identity key add|revoke`), and WHY validity is merged-log-position (epoch) not\n  wall-clock.\n- **Provider-neutral Jira mapping**: outbound assignee/reporter by opaque accountId, the\n  `/user/search` bootstrap, and the **Modify-Reporter** permission constraint +\n  documented degradation.\n- **Opt-in enforcement**: `identity.require_authenticated`, the write-gate, and the\n  crucial **\"the merge-gate is the control; the local write-gate is UX-only\"** caveat;\n  replay-never-rejects; `rebar verify-authorship`.\n\n### 2. ADR `docs/adr/0045-authenticated-identity.md`\nRecords the load-bearing decisions and their rationale/alternatives:\n- **git-bug-style entity**: identity as a first-class event-sourced ticket entity\n  (reusing the exempt-type substrate) rather than a side table.\n- **Opaque-id keying**: mappings keyed on the provider's stable opaque id, NEVER email.\n- **In-band TOFU**: trust-on-first-use genesis keys carried in-band on the identity,\n  with a signed rotation chain (filling git-bug's IsProtected), and era-scoped validity.\n\n### 3. Docs index\nAdd `docs/identity.md` (and the ADR per the ADR-dir convention) to the docs index so\nthe docs-index completeness gate stays green.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `docs/identity.md` exists and covers ALL of: the identity model, tiers, opt-in\n  enforcement + the merge-gate-is-the-control caveat, Jira accountId mapping +\n  Modify-Reporter constraint, key-rotation/era-scoping, and the provider-neutral seam.\n- [ ] `docs/adr/0045-authenticated-identity.md` exists and records the git-bug-entity,\n  opaque-id-keying, and in-band-TOFU decisions (context / decision / consequences).\n- [ ] The docs-index completeness gate passes (`python scripts/check_docs_index.py\n  --check` exits 0) with the new docs indexed.\n\n## file_impact\n- `docs/identity.md` (new operator/agent guide)\n- `docs/adr/0045-authenticated-identity.md` (new ADR)\n- the docs index file (add the new docs so check_docs_index passes)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783868658002427001,"uuid":"80fe1e2f-4f96-40fa-8ea6-79bec0d13e58"}